line_1: And tread on one another's Heel.
line_2: Where ever since the Seasons wheel,

line_1: The insults of the dancer's heel.
And twenty winters scarce suffic'd to heel.
line_2: You will not then those self-reproaches feel,

line_1: She'll clap the Door against your parting Heel.
line_2: But round ere night her giddy Passions wheel,

line_1: And aid his vengeance at the pois'ner's heel —
line_2: With pleasure guard him from a world of ill,

line_1: A gay dragoon with spur on heel,
line_2: And brandished blade of flashing steel;

line_1: So's the Heel-piece to the heel;
line_2: As the needle to the steel,

line_1: Thin be his yielding soal, and low his heel,
line_2: So shall he nimbly bound, and safely wheel.
